Feature: a spike that uncovers an unanticipated hazard records it in the finding and files it as a fresh bead

  Lifecycle stage 4 (Verdict) — ADR-029 D1 stage 4, ADR-030 consequences, PDR-016. A
  spike captures findings beyond its plan, including any new hazard it surfaces that was
  not part of the original hypothesis (the fabro spike surfaced fabro's unconditional
  edges masking a failed node as SUCCEEDED). An unanticipated hazard is recorded in the
  spike's findings document and filed as a fresh lead bead so it is tracked and not
  re-litigated — distinct from the spike bead and from any graduation bead. This is a
  LEAD-PROCESS behavior pinning the lead's findings-plus-registry discipline; there is no
  BC addressee.
  @scenario_hash:e6f84dc40468cc03
  Scenario: a spike that surfaces an unanticipated hazard records it in the finding and files a fresh bead for it
    Given a spike whose execution uncovers a hazard that was not part of its original hypothesis
    When the spike records its verdict and findings beyond the plan
    Then the new hazard is recorded in the spike's findings document as a finding beyond the plan
    And the new hazard is filed as a fresh lead bead distinct from the spike bead and from any graduation bead
